[src:probability-theory/characteristic-function-probability-theory] There is also interest in finding similar simple criteria for when a given function φ could be the characteristic function of some random variable.
[src:probability-theory/characteristic-function-probability-theory] The central result here is Bochner’s theorem, although its usefulness is limited because the main condition of the theorem, non-negative definiteness, is very hard to verify.
[src:probability-theory/characteristic-function-probability-theory] Other theorems also exist, such as Khinchine’s, Mathias’s, or Cramér’s, although their application is just as difficult.
