[src:probability-theory/characteristic-function-probability-theory] Because of the continuity theorem, characteristic functions are used in the most frequently seen proof of the central limit theorem.
[src:probability-theory/characteristic-function-probability-theory] The main technique involved in making calculations with a characteristic function is recognizing the function as the characteristic function of a particular distribution.
[src:probability-theory/characteristic-function-probability-theory] Characteristic functions are particularly useful for dealing with linear functions of independent random variables.
